reviews.review_text: Crazy to hear this show the way I heard it that evening. To me this was a top notch effort that stood out among some pretty stellar efforts over the years.  I had seen most of the shows that summer.  I was on my way back east and stopped in Iowa on the way.  What a treat.  The stella stuck out as a special version along with the eyes, the first set Stagger Lee and miracle bertha.  I've always been partial to a kickin Aiko especially in a venue the size of this field house.  This show had a number "veteran" aspects.  High energy and well well worth a spot in your collection.

best eyes I have to agree with what is said,  The version of eyes really stuck to me.  I liked the sped of tempo to give it just enough edge to make it raw but not destroy the song.  I feel also that the version of Stella blue was one of my favorite.  To bad i was not alive then but this recording brought new birth do these excellent songs.  ecspecially roses. and lost sailor

vg show, vg rec Vg show, agree with other reviews.
The recording is very good as well. Very close to stage, it captures an interesting mix of PA and actual stage sound.

Interesting We traveled to Iowa City from the Alpine Valley shows in Wisconsin. I accidentally over indulged on the colors so the show did not make it into my organic hard drive very well.  Do remember the Iowa State troopers posted around the mezzanine looking pale and freaked out.  Interesting ride back to Chicago on my motorcycle afterwards....
